http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Madurai/AIADMK-meet-lures-youth/article13993977.ece

Hundreds of youngsters, mostly men, gathered at a meeting organised a by the All India Anna Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam (AIADMK) on The Madura College grounds here on Sunday evening, during which the party sources claimed that 25,000 youngsters joined the party.Finance Minister O. Panneerselvam, Electricity Minister ‘Natham’ R. Viswanathan and senior party functionaries attended the meeting for which Minister for Cooperation and party’s Madurai urban secretary ‘Sellur’ K. Raju made the arrangements. Heaping praises on Chief Minister Jayalalithaa for carrying out numerous welfare measures for the people, Mr. Panneerselvam and Mr. Viswanathan said that the people would certainly vote Ms. Jayalalithaa back to power in the Assembly polls.They pointed out that the government had allocated a considerable chunk of every year’s budget for education. Mr. Panneerselvam said that students were happy with the government for distributing laptops, uniforms, textbooks and bicycles to assist them in their education. Earlier, performances by television artistes from popular comedy shows were carried out to entertain the youngsters.